body_html:
OK, that's great. The build/install should have worked. I never had to do this before, but try to uninstall first before installing. And maybe remove /tmp/tensorflow_pkg before you run the pip building script.

The error you are seeing is because the _pywrap_tensorflow_internal.so has not been updated. If you figure out how to rebuild the PIP install then it should work.

body:
OK, that's great. The build/install should have worked. I never had to do this before, but try to uninstall first before installing. And maybe remove /tmp/tensorflow_pkg before you run the pip building script.

The error you are seeing is because the `_pywrap_tensorflow_internal.so` has not been updated. If you figure out how to rebuild the PIP install then it should work.
